{{Infobox person | name = Nick Thune | image = Nick_Thune.jpg | caption = Thune performing at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre|UCB Theatre]] in [[Los Angeles]], January 2010 | birth_name = Nicholas Ivan Thune | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|12|08}} | birth_place = [[Seattle, Washington]], U.S. | occupation = Actor, comedian, musician | years_active = | website = {{URL|http://nickthune.com/|NickThune.com}} }}
'''Nicholas Ivan Thune''' (born December 8, 1979) is an American actor, comedian, and musician.
==Career== Thune was born in [[Seattle, Washington]],<ref name="earwolf">{{Cite web |url=http://www.earwolf.com/person/nick-thune |title=Nick Thune |date=5 May 2011 |website=Earwolf |access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> to parents Erik and Cindy Thune. He has one sister and twin brothers. At age 24, Thune moved to [[Los Angeles]] to pursue his career in [[Stand-up comedy|stand-up]]. He has performed on ''[[The Tonight Show]]'' eight times, and was featured in a ''[[Comedy Central Presents]]'' special in 2007.<ref name="cc">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cc.com/comedians/nick-thune |title=Nick Thune |website=Comedy Central Stand-Up |access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> Aside from numerous stand up gigs, he has also had roles in the movies ''[[Knocked Up]]'' and ''[[Unaccompanied Minors]]''.<ref name="earwolf" />
In February 2009, Thune performed at the DTD Reality concert at the [[University of Southern California]].<ref name="loud">{{Cite web |url=http://www.loudletters.com/ll/rest/celebrityprofile/3A/Nick%20thune |title=Nick Thune profile |website=Loud Letters |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713234423/http://www.loudletters.com/ll/rest/celebrityprofile/3A/Nick%20thune |archive-date=13 July 2011 |access-date=12 March 2017}}</ref>
Thune's debut album ''[[Thick Noon]]'' was released on February 23, 2010 by [[Comedy Central Records]].<ref name="earwolf"/>
Thune was cast as a lead in the 2010 [[NBC]] pilot for ''Beach Lane'' starring opposite [[Matthew Broderick]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/04/nick-thune-enters-nbcs-beach-lane/ |title=Nick Thune Enters NBC's 'Beach Lane' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=17 April 2010 |website=Deadline |publisher=Penske Business Media, LLC |access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> However, the pilot was not picked up as a series.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tv.broadwayworld.com/article/NBC_Cancels_Matthew_Broderick_Pilot_Beach_Lane_20100513 |title=NBC Cancels Matthew Broderick Pilot, 'Beach Lane' |date=13 May 2010 |website=Broadway World |publisher=Wisdom Digital Media |access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> He has since made guest appearances on the comedy programs ''[[Traffic Light (TV series)|Traffic Light]]'' and ''[[Happy Endings (TV series)|Happy Endings]]'' in 2011, and ''[[Don't Trust the B---- in Apartment 23]]'' in 2012.
In 2017, Thune starred in ''[[Dave Made a Maze]]'', playing the titular character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/238841/fantasy-horror-collide-dave-made-maze-trailer/|title=Fantasy and Horror Collide in Dave Made a Maze Trailer|last=Barkan|first=Jonathan|publisher=Dread Central|date=6 July 2017|accessdate=6 July 2017}}</ref> He also starred in the film ''[[People You May Know]]'', directed by [[Sherwin Shilati]].<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5318534/?ref_=ext_shr_eml_tt</ref>
